org.aludratest.service.gui.component.impl
Class DefaultGUIComponentFactory

java.lang.Object
  org.aludratest.service.gui.component.impl.DefaultGUIComponentFactory
All Implemented Interfaces:
GUIComponentFactory
@Component(role=GUIComponentFactory.class,
           hint="default",
           instantiationStrategy="per-lookup")
public class DefaultGUIComponentFactory
extends Object
implements GUIComponentFactory

Default implementation of the GUIComponentFactory interface. Uses Plexus to instantiate the components. GUI service implementors can subclass this class to provide own component implementor classes or additional component configuration.

Author:
falbrech

configureForGUIService

public void configureForGUIService(AludraContext context,
                                   ComponentId<? extends AludraGUI> guiComponentId)
Configures this component factory. It requires an AludraContext and a component ID to query the context for to get the AludraGUI service to use. This is required to get the dynamic proxy for the service, not the service itself.

Parameters:
context - Aludra context to use.
guiComponentId - Component ID to query the context for to get an AludraGUI implementation.

getImplementorClass

protected <T extends GUIComponent> Class<? extends T> getImplementorClass(Class<T> componentClass)
Returns the implementor class for the given component class. Subclasses can override to specify own implementation classes, but you must also override getRoleHint().

Parameters:
componentClass - Class of the component, e.g. Button.class.
Returns:
The implementing component class, or null if no implementor class is available for the given component class. Do not throw any exception; the calling method will deal with this.

getRoleHint

protected String getRoleHint()
Returns the role hint which is used by this component factory. If you want to register your own implementations of the component classes, you also have to override this method to avoid name clashes in the internal Plexus component registry.

Returns:
The role hint to use for this component factory.

configureComponent

protected void configureComponent(GUIComponent component,
                                  Locator locator,
                                  Class<?> componentClass,
                                  String elementName)
Configures the given freshly instantiated component to use the given identifiers. Subclasses can add more configuration logic, but should always invoke the super implementation.

Parameters:
component - Component to configure.
locator - Locator to set in the component.
componentClass - Component class identifying the type of the component, e.g. Button.class.
elementName - Element name which was set in the factory method call or automatically determined if possible, or null.
